 {"id":"franken_networkx-ea2l","title":"parity: graph classes should expose nbunch_iter","description":"Graph, DiGraph, MultiGraph, and MultiDiGraph currently lack NetworkX's nbunch_iter() helper entirely. Upstream graph classes expose nbunch_iter(['a','z']) -> ['a'], while FrankenNetworkX raises AttributeError. Match the upstream node-bunch helper contract across the core graph classes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:44:50.841826346Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T21:30:02.384200568Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T21:30:02.381781750Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-ebkj","title":"parity: MultiGraph and MultiDiGraph edge containment should reject 2-tuple membership","description":"MultiGraph.edges and MultiDiGraph.edges currently report ('a', 'b') in G.edges as True, while upstream NetworkX returns False unless the keyed multiedge is queried through the keyed edge view. Preserve the upstream multigraph containment contract so 2-tuple membership does not silently match any keyed edge.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:51:34.697010625Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:51:34.697010625Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
